## Traps (repo-level)

- `pytest --timeout-method=signal` hangs on asyncio selector loops;
  use `--timeout-method=thread`.
- Pre-commit hook `pytest-check` resolves to worktree-absolute
  paths and fails in isolated worktrees. Use `git -c core.hooksPath=
  /dev/null commit` with bypass documented in commit body per
  `rules/git.md` § Pre-Commit Hook Workarounds.
- SQLite `UpdateNode`/`UpsertNode` return metadata (filter,
  fields, rows_affected), NOT the row. PostgreSQL returns the
  row via RETURNING. Read-back via `self.read()` is the
  dialect-portable pattern (established by #490 fix in
  `features/express.py`).
- Worktree dispatches silently base on old commits. Before
  cherry-picking any `worktree-agent-*` branch, check
  `git merge-base <branch> main`.

